The article discusses Vice President Joe Biden's report on the Summer of Recovery Act activity. It highlights the surge in infrastructure projects that will be underway during the summer, creating jobs and promoting economic growth. The Recovery Act has already put over $620 billion to work, providing tax relief, financial assistance, and funding for technology, innovation, and infrastructure projects. The report also mentions the increase in highway projects, clean and drinking water projects, home weatherization, and projects at national parks. It lists several milestones that will be achieved during the summer, such as the groundbreaking of the 10,000th road project and the completion of community health care centers. The article states that the job impact of the Recovery Act will continue to climb, with the target of 3.5 million jobs by the end of 2010. The estimates from the non-partisan Congressional Budget Office have confirmed or exceeded the Council of Economic Advisers' estimates.